Long ago, I believe there was some evidence that Google or other search 
engines considered only the root /robots.txt, without any redirects, as 
being the authentic directive to apply to the whole server.

 From looking at how Google handles a [site:www.swims.nhs.uk] query, it 
appears they are following this redirect and respecting the found robots.

To match webmaster expectations set by Google, Heritrix should do the 
same. I&#39;ve made an issue to track this:

  https://webarchive.jira.com/browse/HER-1263

- Gordon

